Wanna see what else he can do?

520
00:47:37,280 --> 00:47:38,110
Watch, watch.

521
00:47:38,360 --> 00:47:41,238
Mr. Jingle? Mr. Jingle,
wanna play fetch?

522
00:47:41,600 --> 00:47:42,953
Wanna play fetch?

523
00:47:43,760 --> 00:47:45,955
Play fetch. Watch, watch, watch.

524
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:07,150
He fetch it every time. Every time.

525
00:48:07,920 --> 00:48:12,436
That's some smart mouse, Del.
Like he a circus mouse or something.

526
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:17,518
Correct. That just what he is too.
He's a circus mouse.

527
00:48:17,760 --> 00:48:19,716
When I get out,
he'll make me rich.

528
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:22,310
You just watch and see
if he don't do that.

529
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:24,710
We play fetch again?

530
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:27,118
PERCY:
Well, well, well.

531
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:29,670
Looks like you found yourself
a new friend.

532
00:48:30,320 --> 00:48:31,594
Don't hurt him.

533
00:48:34,160 --> 00:48:35,434
Is that the one I chased?

534
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:37,432
Yeah, that's the one.

535
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:41,037
Only Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.

536
00:48:42,040 --> 00:48:42,995
Is that so?

537
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:45,832
Del's been asking for a box.

538
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:48,272
Thinks the mouse will sleep in it.

539
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:50,273
Might keep it for a pet.

540
00:48:52,600 --> 00:48:53,794
What do you think?

541
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:58,635
You know what?
We ought to find a cigar box...

542
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:03,557
...and get some cotton batting
from the dispensary to line it with.

543
00:49:06,680 --> 00:49:08,716
That should do real nice.

544
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:20,069
Man said get a cigar box.

545
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:30,753
SECRETARY:
Morning.

546
00:49:35,360 --> 00:49:36,793
Hal, you wanted to see me?

547
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:38,754
Yeah.

548
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:40,759
Close the door.

549
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:49,432
So you know...

550
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:53,235
...you got a new prisoner
coming in here tomorrow.

551
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:55,958
"William Wharton."

552
00:49:56,640 --> 00:49:58,198
He's what you call...

553
00:49:58,520 --> 00:50:00,431
...a problem child.

554
00:50:01,200 --> 00:50:04,749
Got "Billy the Kid" tattooed
on his left arm.

555
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:08,879
Been rambling all over the state
last few years...

556
00:50:09,280 --> 00:50:11,396
...causing all kinds of trouble.

557
00:50:12,120 --> 00:50:13,997
Finally hit the big time.

558
00:50:15,320 --> 00:50:18,437
Killed three people in a holdup.

559
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:20,756
One of them a pregnant woman.

560
00:50:23,120 --> 00:50:25,031
Bad news all around.

561
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:28,194
Hal?

562
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:40,074
It's a tumor, Paul.

563
00:50:41,680 --> 00:50:43,398
A brain tumor.

564
00:50:45,040 --> 00:50:46,155
They got...

565
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:48,951
...x-ray pictures of it.

566
00:50:50,320 --> 00:50:52,754
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

567
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:56,594
And...

568
00:50:57,680 --> 00:50:59,113
...way down...

569
00:51:00,880 --> 00:51:02,996
...deep inside,
where they can't operate.

570
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:06,552
I haven't told her.

571
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:10,157
I can't think how.

572
00:51:13,760 --> 00:51:15,830
For the life of me, Paul...

573
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:20,118
...I can't think how
to tell my wife...

574
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:25,391
...she's going to die.

575
00:52:30,720 --> 00:52:31,835
(GROANS)

576
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:48,596
Oh, oh, God.

577
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:50,713
Oh, God.

578
00:52:54,440 --> 00:52:55,714
I'm going.

579
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:56,790
What?

580
00:52:57,040 --> 00:52:59,759
To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

581
00:53:00,080 --> 00:53:01,559
Today.

582
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:04,639
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

583
00:53:04,960 --> 00:53:06,109
That bad?

584
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:08,153
Oh, yeah.

585
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:31,470
The boy's doped to the gills.

586
00:53:34,360 --> 00:53:35,509
Hand me them clothes.

587
00:53:38,440 --> 00:53:40,237
William Wharton?

588
00:53:40,560 --> 00:53:41,356
Hey!

589
00:53:41,920 --> 00:53:43,717
You put on these clothes now.

590
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:52,589
We'll have to do this.

591
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:56,233
PERCY:
Hellraiser, huh?

592
00:53:56,480 --> 00:53:58,994
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

593
00:54:00,960 --> 00:54:02,029
Hey!

594
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:06,269
You've been declared competent, son.
You know what that means?

595
00:54:06,960 --> 00:54:08,632
You're gonna ride the lightning.

596
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:13,153
Shut up, give us a hand.

597
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,638
Hellraiser.

598
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:46,759
DEL:
You don't look so good.

599
00:54:48,640 --> 00:54:50,517
Look like you're running you a fever.

600
00:54:50,760 --> 00:54:52,079
(PHONE RINGS)

601
00:54:56,080 --> 00:54:57,593
COFFEY:
Boss Edgecomb?

602
00:54:59,040 --> 00:55:00,871
I needs to see you down here.

603
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,595
I got things to tend to, John Coffey.

604
00:55:08,120 --> 00:55:11,396
You just stay still in your cell.

605
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:23,674
E Block.

606
00:55:58,440 --> 00:55:59,839
DEAN:
Come on, let's go.

607
00:56:01,040 --> 00:56:03,031
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

608
00:56:17,120 --> 00:56:18,314
Careful.

609
00:56:21,720 --> 00:56:22,516
Careful.

610
00:56:22,760 --> 00:56:23,556
PERCY:
Step up.

611
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:24,716
Step up.

612
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:05,034
Ain't this a party now?

613
00:57:05,440 --> 00:57:06,475
BILL Y: Is it or what?
-Let him go.

614
00:57:06,720 --> 00:57:08,233
-Shoot him.
-See who you hit.

615
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:09,879
DEAN:
Shoot the son of a bitch.

616
00:57:10,160 --> 00:57:10,956
Shoot him!

617
00:57:11,160 --> 00:57:13,674
Hit him, Percy!
Goddamn it! Hit him.

618
00:57:13,920 --> 00:57:15,273
Hit me, you limp noodle.

619
00:57:15,520 --> 00:57:16,350
Hit him, Percy!

620
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:17,635
Goddamn it, hit him!

621
00:57:17,920 --> 00:57:19,114
Come on, Percy. Hit me.

622
00:57:19,920 --> 00:57:20,716
I'm warning you.

623
00:57:20,960 --> 00:57:22,279
You warning me?

624
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:23,630
PAUL:
I'm warning you!

625
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:25,791
BILL Y: You're warning me?!
DEAN: Shoot him!

626
00:57:26,040 --> 00:57:27,268
BILL Y:
Well, come on...

627
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:34,589
You're a big fucker.

628
00:57:35,760 --> 00:57:37,159
Where'd you come from?

629
00:57:47,320 --> 00:57:49,675
BRUTAL: Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

630
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:51,433
All right. Let it breathe.

631
00:57:51,960 --> 00:57:53,996
That's it. Just breathe.
Just breathe.

632
00:57:55,800 --> 00:57:57,472
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

633
00:57:57,720 --> 00:58:00,473
DEAN: Didn't see it coming.
BRUTAL: Come on, boy, breathe.

634
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:02,631
Come on. Just breathe.

635
00:58:05,400 --> 00:58:07,470
We thought he was doped.

636
00:58:08,680 --> 00:58:11,752
Didn't we? Didn't we, all of us,
think he was doped?

637
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:13,672
You didn't ask?

638
00:58:14,880 --> 00:58:16,677
PAUL:
I guess that's not a mistake...

639
00:58:17,040 --> 00:58:20,112
...you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

640
00:58:33,640 --> 00:58:37,076
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

641
00:58:37,560 --> 00:58:40,836
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

642
00:58:41,080 --> 00:58:43,548
Say the situation's under control.
It's not a story.

643
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:46,268
He won't appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

644
00:58:46,520 --> 00:58:48,636
What about you?
You're about to collapse.

645
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:52,077
I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

646
00:58:52,840 --> 00:58:54,717
Go on now. Go.

647
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:05,032
Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

648
00:59:29,600 --> 00:59:32,876
COFFEY:
Boss, I needs to see you down here.

649
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:39,397
PAUL:
This is not a good time, John Coffey...

650
00:59:39,640 --> 00:59:41,471
...not a good time at all.

651
00:59:41,720 --> 00:59:45,633
COFFEY: But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

652
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:08,028
Closer.

653
01:00:08,560 --> 01:00:10,516
You know you ain't
supposed to do that.

654
01:00:12,080 --> 01:00:13,991
Mind your business, Del.

655
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:25,196
What do you want, John Coffey?

656
01:00:26,200 --> 01:00:27,269
Just to help it.

657
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,159
COFFEY:
Don't be afraid.

658
01:00:32,760 --> 01:00:33,670
Help!

659
01:00:34,480 --> 01:00:35,276
Help!

660
01:00:35,520 --> 01:00:37,158
Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

661
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:38,753
DEL:
Help!

662
01:00:39,000 --> 01:00:40,035
What are you doing?

663
01:00:44,600 --> 01:00:46,318
DEL:
Boss Howell! Help!

664
01:00:47,000 --> 01:00:48,672
Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

665
01:00:58,560 --> 01:00:59,993
(YELLS)

666
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:08,716
DEL:
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

667
01:01:09,000 --> 01:01:11,798
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

668
01:01:12,040 --> 01:01:14,508
Del, for chrissakes, shut up!

669
01:01:16,240 --> 01:01:17,958
(COUGHS)

670
01:01:59,200 --> 01:02:01,395
What did you just do to me?

671
01:02:03,240 --> 01:02:04,912
I helped it.

672
01:02:05,880 --> 01:02:07,472
Didn't I help it?

673
01:02:08,560 --> 01:02:10,676
I just took it back, is all.

674
01:02:11,480 --> 01:02:13,835
Awful tired now, boss.

675
01:02:14,320 --> 01:02:15,912
Dog-tired.

676
01:02:39,080 --> 01:02:41,992
DEL:
Boss, what that man do to you?

677
01:03:07,400 --> 01:03:10,597
(URINATES)

678
01:03:41,880 --> 01:03:44,599
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

679
01:03:46,280 --> 01:03:48,919
Oh, not too bad.

680
01:03:50,120 --> 01:03:51,838
JAN:
What did the doctor say?

681
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:55,632
You know doctors.

682
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:57,837
Gobbledygook, mostly.

683
01:03:58,920 --> 01:04:00,239
JAN:
Gobbledygook.

684
01:04:14,880 --> 01:04:16,438
Having stew tonight.

685
01:04:26,280 --> 01:04:27,918
What are you doing?

686
01:04:34,320 --> 01:04:36,117
What does it feel like?

687
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:39,269
Well, I know what it feels like.

688
01:04:42,800 --> 01:04:44,631
It feels great.

689
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:57,358
(JAN MOANS)

690
01:05:04,160 --> 01:05:06,469
(PAUL MOANS)

691
01:05:17,560 --> 01:05:19,118
-Paul?
-Yeah?

692
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:22,519
Not that I'm complaining...

693
01:05:23,640 --> 01:05:27,155
...but we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

694
01:05:27,440 --> 01:05:29,715
Yeah, we did, at your mom's.

695
01:05:31,120 --> 01:05:33,031
Wanna tell me what's going on?

696
01:05:36,720 --> 01:05:37,675
Well...

697
01:05:39,240 --> 01:05:41,151
...see, the thing is...

698
01:05:42,320 --> 01:05:45,756
...I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

699
01:05:48,800 --> 01:05:51,439
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

700
01:05:51,680 --> 01:05:55,958
I'm thinking of taking the morning
off sick. You cover the fort for me?

701
01:05:56,920 --> 01:05:59,070
That's swell. Thanks.

702
01:05:59,320 --> 01:06:01,834
Yeah, I'm sure I'll feel better.

703
01:06:02,040 --> 01:06:03,155
Okay.

704
01:06:09,720 --> 01:06:11,631
You're sure you ought to do this?

705
01:06:13,160 --> 01:06:15,276
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

706
01:06:31,480 --> 01:06:34,313
Burt, you got some company.

707
01:06:34,960 --> 01:06:36,518
Can I offer you a cold drink?

708
01:06:36,760 --> 01:06:39,672
Yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

709
01:06:40,000 --> 01:06:42,912
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home.

710
01:06:43,160 --> 01:06:44,752
Hope I'm not troubling you.

711
01:06:45,440 --> 01:06:47,431
Well, that depends, Mr...?

712
01:06:47,680 --> 01:06:51,468
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

713
01:06:52,680 --> 01:06:53,908
The Green Mile.

714
01:06:54,160 --> 01:06:57,152
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

715
01:06:57,880 --> 01:06:59,552
I'd like to ask you about one.

716
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:03,551
-Have a seat.
-Thank you.

717
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:08,990
Which client?

718
01:07:11,160 --> 01:07:13,799
BURT:
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

719
01:07:14,040 --> 01:07:15,314
John Coffey.

720
01:07:16,520 --> 01:07:17,589
Coffey.

721
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:19,149
Causing you problems?

722
01:07:19,640 --> 01:07:22,996
Can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion...

723
01:07:23,240 --> 01:07:24,992
...but other than that...

724
01:07:25,240 --> 01:07:28,357
He cries, does he?
Got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

725
01:07:28,600 --> 01:07:30,033
You know what he did.

726
01:07:30,720 --> 01:07:32,631
PAUL:
I read the court transcript.

727
01:07:33,520 --> 01:07:34,316
Thank you, missus.

728
01:07:34,520 --> 01:07:36,158
My pleasure.

729
01:07:37,000 --> 01:07:37,796
Kids!

730
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:40,150
CYNTHIA: Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

731
01:07:40,440 --> 01:07:41,589
KIDS:
Coming, Mama!

732
01:07:41,840 --> 01:07:44,832
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

733
01:07:45,440 --> 01:07:47,670
I wonder if he did anything
like that before.

734
01:07:49,040 --> 01:07:50,917
Why? Has he said anything?

735
01:07:51,160 --> 01:07:54,152
No, but a man who does
a thing like that...

736
01:07:54,400 --> 01:07:58,075
...has often developed a taste for it
over time. It occurred to me...

737
01:07:58,320 --> 01:08:02,029
...that it might be easy enough to
follow his back trail. Find out.

738
01:08:02,840 --> 01:08:06,435
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

739
01:08:06,680 --> 01:08:09,513
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

740
01:08:09,760 --> 01:08:11,751
Believe me, we tried.

741
01:08:12,600 --> 01:08:14,670
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

742
01:08:15,480 --> 01:08:16,799
How can that be?

743
01:08:17,040 --> 01:08:20,999
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

744
01:08:21,280 --> 01:08:25,114
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

745
01:08:25,400 --> 01:08:28,358
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere.

746
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:31,310
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

747
01:08:32,120 --> 01:08:33,678
He is...

748
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:35,991
...strange, I admit.

749
01:08:36,320 --> 01:08:40,472
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

750
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:43,189
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

751
01:08:43,480 --> 01:08:46,153
I deal with them day in and day out.

752
01:08:46,920 --> 01:08:49,434
You didn't come to ask me
whether he killed before.

753
01:08:49,680 --> 01:08:52,513
You came to see if I think
he did it at all.

754
01:08:53,880 --> 01:08:54,676
Do you?

755
01:08:56,600 --> 01:08:58,636
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

756
01:08:58,880 --> 01:09:00,836
He was found with the victims
in his arms.

757
01:09:01,080 --> 01:09:02,798
And yet you defended him.

758
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:06,228
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

759
01:09:06,680 --> 01:09:08,193
CYNTHIA:
Kids! Lunch!

760
01:09:08,440 --> 01:09:09,634
Y'all listen to your mama!

761
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:15,638
I'll tell you something.

762
01:09:16,640 --> 01:09:20,030
You listen close too, because it
might be something you need to know.

763
01:09:20,280 --> 01:09:21,554
I'm listening.

764
01:09:22,960 --> 01:09:23,995
We had us a dog.

765
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,871
Just a sweet mongrel.

766
01:09:27,120 --> 01:09:28,553
You know the kind.

767
01:09:29,840 --> 01:09:33,150
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

768
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:35,638
You get to know it.

769
01:09:35,920 --> 01:09:40,038
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use...

770
01:09:40,280 --> 01:09:43,670
...but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

771
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:49,039
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you
never have to find out any different.

772
01:09:50,080 --> 01:09:52,196
My wife and I were not so lucky.

773
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:55,559
Caleb, come here for a second.

774
01:09:56,880 --> 01:09:58,029
Come here.

775
01:09:59,480 --> 01:10:00,629
Please, son.

776
01:10:02,160 --> 01:10:04,594
He still has the one good eye.

777
01:10:05,840 --> 01:10:07,990
I suppose he's lucky...

778
01:10:08,240 --> 01:10:10,515
...not to be completely blind.

779
01:10:13,080 --> 01:10:16,709
We get down on our knees and thank God
