Sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

1796
02:41:21,760 --> 02:41:24,832
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

1797
02:41:26,520 --> 02:41:28,954
I'm sorry for what I am.

1798
02:41:40,520 --> 02:41:42,112
Please, boss...

1799
02:41:43,520 --> 02:41:46,080
...don't put that thing over my face.

1800
02:41:47,200 --> 02:41:49,475
Don't put me in the dark.

1801
02:41:50,200 --> 02:41:52,475
I's afraid of the dark.

1802
02:42:01,720 --> 02:42:03,358
All right, John.

1803
02:42:22,720 --> 02:42:25,553
SINGS:
Heaven, I'm in heaven

1804
02:42:25,800 --> 02:42:28,473
Heaven, heaven

1805
02:42:28,720 --> 02:42:30,472
I'm in heaven

1806
02:42:31,000 --> 02:42:33,468
Heaven, heaven

1807
02:42:33,720 --> 02:42:35,358
I'm in heaven

1808
02:42:55,440 --> 02:42:56,953
John Coffey...

1809
02:42:57,920 --> 02:43:00,912
...electricity shall pass through
your body until you are dead...

1810
02:43:01,160 --> 02:43:03,196
...in accordance with state law.

1811
02:43:05,520 --> 02:43:09,069
May God have mercy on your soul.

1812
02:43:41,960 --> 02:43:43,109
Paul...

1813
02:43:46,200 --> 02:43:48,031
You have to say it.

1814
02:43:49,680 --> 02:43:51,830
You have to give the order.

1815
02:44:09,120 --> 02:44:11,350
COFFEY:
He killed them with they love.

1816
02:44:11,600 --> 02:44:16,151
That's how it is every day
all over the world.

1817
02:44:29,440 --> 02:44:30,793
Roll on two.

1818
02:46:11,160 --> 02:46:14,436
PAUL: It was the last execution
I ever took part in.

1819
02:46:14,680 --> 02:46:18,229
I just couldn't do it anymore
after that. Brutal either.

1820
02:46:19,400 --> 02:46:23,871
We both transferred out,
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

1821
02:46:24,120 --> 02:46:25,792
It was all right.

1822
02:46:26,440 --> 02:46:29,238
"Catch them young" became my motto.

1823
02:46:32,360 --> 02:46:33,429
You don't believe me.

1824
02:46:34,240 --> 02:46:36,708
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

1825
02:46:37,480 --> 02:46:39,471
-lt's just that...
-lt's quite a story.

1826
02:46:39,720 --> 02:46:41,870
It's quite a story.

1827
02:46:42,240 --> 02:46:44,515
One thing I don't understand.

1828
02:46:44,760 --> 02:46:46,432
You said you and Jan...

1829
02:46:46,680 --> 02:46:50,070
...had a grown son in 1935.

1830
02:46:50,360 --> 02:46:51,793
Is that right?

1831
02:46:52,160 --> 02:46:54,037
The math doesn't work, does it?

1832
02:46:59,520 --> 02:47:01,954
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

1833
02:47:21,840 --> 02:47:23,159
PAUL:
Watch your step.

1834
02:47:23,640 --> 02:47:25,870
Now let your eyes adjust.

1835
02:47:37,240 --> 02:47:38,229
There.

1836
02:47:41,880 --> 02:47:43,518
Wake up, old fella.

1837
02:47:43,800 --> 02:47:44,994
Wake up.

1838
02:47:48,480 --> 02:47:52,155
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

1839
02:47:56,160 --> 02:47:57,479
Come over here, boy.

1840
02:47:57,920 --> 02:48:00,195
Come on over here and see this lady.

1841
02:48:03,000 --> 02:48:05,912
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

1842
02:48:11,640 --> 02:48:13,517
(IN FRENCH)

1843
02:48:27,640 --> 02:48:30,108
PAUL:
Go on, you can do it.

1844
02:48:36,920 --> 02:48:41,232
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

1845
02:48:42,000 --> 02:48:45,754
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

1846
02:48:51,960 --> 02:48:55,509
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

1847
02:48:55,880 --> 02:49:00,556
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly...

1848
02:49:00,800 --> 02:49:02,995
...well, John could feel that,
you know.

1849
02:49:03,240 --> 02:49:06,516
And I think a part of...

1850
02:49:06,760 --> 02:49:09,320
...whatever magic was inside of him...

1851
02:49:09,600 --> 02:49:12,751
...just leapt into my tiny friend here.

1852
02:49:13,880 --> 02:49:15,791
As for me...

1853
02:49:16,920 --> 02:49:19,388
...John had to give me
a part of himself...

1854
02:49:19,640 --> 02:49:21,710
...a gift, the way he saw it...

1855
02:49:22,040 --> 02:49:25,350
...so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

1856
02:49:27,680 --> 02:49:29,750
When John did that...

1857
02:49:31,160 --> 02:49:33,435
...when he took my hand...

1858
02:49:34,400 --> 02:49:38,075
...a part of the power
that worked through him...

1859
02:49:39,000 --> 02:49:40,797
...spilled into me.

1860
02:49:41,120 --> 02:49:42,872
He...what?

1861
02:49:43,360 --> 02:49:46,716
He infected you with life?

1862
02:49:48,200 --> 02:49:50,475
It's as good a word as any.

1863
02:49:51,880 --> 02:49:54,633
He infected us both,
didn't he, Mr. Jingles?

1864
02:49:54,880 --> 02:49:56,313
With life.

1865
02:50:00,160 --> 02:50:03,152
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

1866
02:50:03,400 --> 02:50:07,552
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

1867
02:50:10,400 --> 02:50:13,949
You mustn't blame John.
He couldn't help what happened.

1868
02:50:14,200 --> 02:50:18,557
He was just a force of nature.

1869
02:50:19,000 --> 02:50:23,039
I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

1870
02:50:24,000 --> 02:50:26,878
Another century come to pass.

1871
02:50:29,520 --> 02:50:33,752
But I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

1872
02:50:34,120 --> 02:50:36,111
Hal and Melinda...

1873
02:50:36,560 --> 02:50:37,879
...Brutus Howell...

1874
02:50:38,120 --> 02:50:40,680
...my wife, my boy.

1875
02:50:43,520 --> 02:50:45,317
And you, Elaine.

1876
02:50:46,240 --> 02:50:47,958
You'll die too.

1877
02:50:49,440 --> 02:50:53,592
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

1878
02:50:55,000 --> 02:50:57,355
It's my atonement, you see.

1879
02:50:57,880 --> 02:50:59,518
It's my punishment...

1880
02:50:59,760 --> 02:51:02,228
...for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning.

1881
02:51:03,880 --> 02:51:06,553
For killing a miracle of God.

1882
02:51:08,000 --> 02:51:10,719
PRIEST:
Almighty, everlasting God...

1883
02:51:11,000 --> 02:51:13,230
...the source of all being and life.

1884
02:51:13,480 --> 02:51:17,632
PAUL: You'll be gone like all the
others. I'll have to stay.

1885
02:51:19,560 --> 02:51:23,599
I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.

1886
02:51:24,320 --> 02:51:28,108
I have no illusions of immortality.

1887
02:51:28,520 --> 02:51:30,875
But I will have wished for death...

1888
02:51:31,600 --> 02:51:33,670
...long before death finds me.

1889
02:51:34,720 --> 02:51:38,395
In truth, I wish for it already.

1890
02:51:39,560 --> 02:51:41,949
(MAN SINGS OVER RADIO)

1891
02:51:49,960 --> 02:51:51,871
Mr. Jingles?

1892
02:52:00,520 --> 02:52:02,590
Where you been?

1893
02:52:03,000 --> 02:52:06,117
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry?

1894
02:52:06,920 --> 02:52:09,275
Let's see if we can find you
something to eat.

1895
02:52:10,360 --> 02:52:13,909
A few crumbs anyway.
I know you'd like that.

1896
02:52:15,360 --> 02:52:16,634
Look at you.

1897
02:52:18,240 --> 02:52:21,915
PAUL: I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.

1898
02:52:22,160 --> 02:52:24,116
And I wait.

1899
02:52:24,960 --> 02:52:27,554
I think about all the people
I've loved...

1900
02:52:27,800 --> 02:52:29,870
...now long gone.

1901
02:52:30,600 --> 02:52:32,875
I think about my beautiful Jan...

1902
02:52:33,120 --> 02:52:35,998
...how I lost her so many years ago.

1903
02:52:37,360 --> 02:52:41,717
And I think about all of us walking
our own Green Mile...

1904
02:52:41,960 --> 02:52:44,554
...each in our own time.

1905
02:52:45,560 --> 02:52:48,597
But one thought
more than any other...

1906
02:52:48,840 --> 02:52:51,400
...keeps me awake most nights:

1907
02:52:52,520 --> 02:52:56,308
If he could make a mouse
live so long...

1908
02:52:56,760 --> 02:52:59,672
...how much longer do I have?

1909
02:53:02,880 --> 02:53:05,474
We each owe a death.

1910
02:53:05,720 --> 02:53:08,109
There are no exceptions.

1911
02:53:08,840 --> 02:53:10,751
But, oh, God...

1912
02:53:11,680 --> 02:53:13,398
...sometimes...

1913
02:53:13,920 --> 02:53:17,435
...the Green Mile seems so long.

1914
